history.content: I'm not sure about 161 specifically, but it seems like the waitlists for other classes were processed before the 9AM start time for adjustment period today. This was probably the case for 161, which means that all declared CS/EECS majors on the waitlist were processed before you.

Hi there, 

You can and should use the validate option to check for course conflicts when enrolling. I would assume the scheduler is doing their job correctly and would discourage you from emailing them "just to be sure". 

Hang in there :)
